i have employees that copy excel cells into confluence pages.

the rendered cells as an HTML table look pretty good as the Rich Text Editor does a good job of taking the HTML and enclosing it in the {html} macro.

but it needs to automatically strip the meta tags and other HTML tags outside the body tags, as these tags corrupt the page and don't allow subsequent edits to the page.

Even though 2.2 won't use jtidy, we need to see what this markup does...
{noformat}
h1. {panel:title=DDM Data and Application Upload Procedures}{panel}
Some text...
h2. *DDM & Cat - Environment Overview*

h2. Support Documents and Information

h2. {panel:title=VERSION 2/ CLASS 3} {panel}
Some text...
h2. {panel:title=VERSION 3/ CLASS 1 AND CLASS 2 AND CHARTVIEWER}{panel} 

{noformat}

Examples of incorrectly-identified missing links:

1. Escaped brackets in wiki markup; e.g., DataRow\[INDEX, DataRowVersion.OriginalVersion\]

2. marked sections

e.g.,

{code}
[HKEY_CURRENT_USER\SOFTWARE\Microsoft\.NETFramework\AssemblyFolders\dotnetCHARTING]@="C:\\Windows\dotnetCHARTING\"
{code}

{digraph}
node [shape = circle];
{digraph}

